author: itv.com
title: Historic re-branding for First Great Western
text:
The company will be known as Great Western Railway from September 20 Credit: Artist Impression First Great Western will re-name their service the Great Western Railway - the name used by Isambard Kingdom Brunel when the line was first constructed.
The announcement came as the great, great, great Grandson of Brunel traced the footsteps of his ancestor to celebrate the electrification of the line.
Last updated Tue 8 Sep 2015 Travel
